<h3>Testing Debian-Installer</h3>

<p>
Debian-Installer images are available for testing purposes. These images
will install Debian's testing distribution (sarge). The Debian-Installer's
<a href="http://cvs.debian.org/debian-installer/doc/INSTALLATION-HOWTO?rev=HEAD&content-type=text/vnd.viewcvs-markup">INSTALLATION HOWTO</a>
includes links to CD and disk images, and a walkthrough of the install
process.
</p>

<p>
Official Net Install CD images are being built, and are
<a href="http://gluck.debian.org/cdimage/testing/netinst/">available</a>:
<ul>
<li><a href="http://gluck.debian.org/cdimage/testing/netinst/i386/sarge-i386-businesscard.iso">debian-installer and doc only, requires net access</a> (50MB)<br></li>
<li><a href="http://gluck.debian.org/cdimage/testing/netinst/i386/sarge-i386-netinst.iso">debian-installer and base system, basic install possible without net access</a> (100MB)<br></li>
<li>Official "testing" full CD images' Jigdo files are also available
at <url "http://gluck.debian.org/cdimage/testing/jigdo-area/">.
They are regularly updated.</li>
</ul>
</p>

<p>
The <a href="ports-status">Ports Status Page</a> tracks the status and
availability of Debian-Installer on different architectures.
</p>

<p>
After testing the Debian-Installer, <em>please</em> send us an
<a href="report-template">installation report</a>, so we can track and fix
and problems you may find.
</p>

<h3>What can I do to help?</h3>

<p>
Debian-Installer is in need of your help. We need both C and
shell hackers in addition to translations, documentation testing.
<ul>
	<li>Sign up to the <a href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-boot/">debian-boot
	mailing list</a> and introduce yourself.</li>
	<li>Get a <a href="cvs">CVS checkout of Debian-Installer</a></li>
	<li>Check the <a href="http://cvs.debian.org/debian-installer/doc/TODO?rev=HEAD&amp;content-type=text/vnd.viewcvs-markup">TODO</a> for tasks needing attention. 
	<li>Fix any of the <a href="http://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/pkgreport.cgi?which=tag&data=d-i&archive=no">d-i tagged bug reports</a>
	in the <a href="http://bugs.debian.org/">Debian BTS</a>.
	
</ul>
</p>

<h3>Contating us</h3>

<p>
The <a href="http://lists.debian.org/debian-boot/">debian-boot
